{
  "stem": "1895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There-- there many Poles who were real bad, they would carry this into the camp as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I would say that in most cases, there was more camaraderie in the camps than outside the camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auschwitz was the culmination of all my experiences.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember when I left Auschwitz one day in November when they evacuated us, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my-- my great dream and desire was to survive, to be a witness.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That was the greatest desire I had, was to survive and be a witness.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For my family, for my friends, and for what I saw in Auschwitz, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and what is indelibly marked in my-- in my brain.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If I live to be 1,000, some of the things that I saw, I remember as if I saw them yesterday.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] There was one point where a [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] troop-- a train came in from Hungary.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And a lot of Hungarian people came out and they were in the Jewish garb.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were religious Orthodox people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a lot of them walked from the ramp into the gas chamber with the prayer books wide open and praying and shaking, praying and shaking.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember we were not allowed to speak to them, even though they passed us by within a few-- they passed us within a few feet.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember one time there was a very learned-looking-- I would say a rabbi, beard, with an open book.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And for some reason, they stopped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was something going on ahead and they stopped for a while.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he looked at me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he looked at me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he said, [NON-ENGLISH]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You're a Jew.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
